com.softwareag.natural.mapconverter

Interface IExtendedIfField


  • public interface IExtendedIfField
    Interface implemented by extended IfField object. It provides additional information for transforming multi-dimensional IfFields into columns of a GRID control.
    Author:
    zim

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IfField getIfField() 
      java.lang.String getMultiDimensionalIndex()
      Returns the multi-dimensional index for the GRID binding.
      java.lang.String getTransformedColumnName()
      Returns the column name which has been applied for this IfField object binding multi-dimensional array items to GRID columns.
      boolean hasMultiDimensionalIndex()
      Returns true if a multi-dimensional index is set for this IfField for the GRID binding.
      boolean hasTransformedColumnName()
      Returns true if a column name has been applied for this IfField object.

    • Method Detail

      • getIfField

        IfField getIfField()

      • getMultiDimensionalIndex

        java.lang.String getMultiDimensionalIndex()
        Returns the multi-dimensional index for the GRID binding. If no index is set null is returned.
        Returns:
        the index or null

      • getTransformedColumnName

        java.lang.String getTransformedColumnName()
        Returns the column name which has been applied for this IfField object binding multi-dimensional array items to GRID columns.
        Returns:
        the column name or null

      • hasMultiDimensionalIndex

        boolean hasMultiDimensionalIndex()
        Returns true if a multi-dimensional index is set for this IfField for the GRID binding.
        Returns:
        true in case a multi-dimensional index is set, false otherwise

      • hasTransformedColumnName

        boolean hasTransformedColumnName()
        Returns true if a column name has been applied for this IfField object. Usually a column name is only applied if this IfField is an item of a multi-dimensional array.
        Returns:
        true in case a column name has been applied, false otherwise
